1 
;Residues ASN G276 and ASN G384 that are next to each other in the sample sequence are not properly linked: distance between C and N is 24.8
;
2 
;Residues ASN H162 and PHE H163 that are next to each other in the sample sequence are not properly linked: distance between C and N is 3.49
;
3 
;Residues SER I233 and ASP I236 that are next to each other in the sample sequence are not properly linked: distance between C and N is 4.93
;
4 
;Residues LYS I355 and ASP I361 that are next to each other in the sample sequence are not properly linked: distance between C and N is 11.86
;
5 
;Residues SER J172 and GLU J195 that are next to each other in the sample sequence are not properly linked: distance between C and N is 28.90
;
6 
;Residues ASP J232 and ASP J236 that are next to each other in the sample sequence are not properly linked: distance between C and N is 8.10
;
7 
;The distance between Residue SER I162 and Residue GLU I195 is 26.14 Angstrom. But there are only 2 residues (not enough sequence) to cover the gap region
